ndia but also shows how connections were imagined over a century of screen exchange. Employing a comparative framework, Govil details the history of influence, traces the nature of interoperability, and textures the contact between Hollywood and Bombay cinema by exploring both the reality and imagination of encounter.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aMotion picture industryxHistoryxCaliforniaxLos Angeles. 0aMotion picture industryxHistoryxIndiaxMumbai. 0aMotion picture industryzCaliforniazLos AngelesxHistory. 0aMotion picture industryzIndiazMumbaixHistory. 0aMotion picturesxInfluencexIndia. 0aMotion picturesxInfluencexUnited StatesxCaliforniaxLos AngelesxIndiaxIndiaxMumbaixUnited States. 0aMotion pictureszIndiaxInfluence. 0aMotion pictureszUnited StatesxInfluence. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP / FUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071187540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814764732423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814764732.jpg  a978-3-11-071187-5  NYUP / FUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK